2598	  \uses{lem:isLocalizedModule_tilde_restrict}
2599	  \textit{Affine engine of \cref{lem:qcoh_section_localization_basicOpen}: the basic-open
2600	  restriction localizes for any module sheaf that is \(\widetilde{N}\) up to isomorphism.}
2601	  Let \(M\) be a sheaf of modules on \(\Spec R\) such that the counit
2602	  \(M.\mathrm{fromTildeΓ}\) is an isomorphism (equivalently, \(M\) lies in the essential image of
2603	  \(\widetilde{(-)}\); Mathlib's \(\mathrm{isIso\_fromTildeΓ\_iff}\)), and let \(f \in R\). Then the
2604	  presheaf restriction of \(M\) from \(\Gamma(M, \top)\) to \(\Gamma(M, D(f))\) is
2605	  \(\mathrm{IsLocalizedModule}(\mathrm{powers}\,f)\) over \(R\).
2606	\end{lemma}
2607	\begin{proof}
2608	  The image of \(M.\mathrm{fromTildeΓ}\) under \(\mathrm{modulesSpecToSheaf}\) is an isomorphism;
2609	  forgetting to the presheaf gives a natural isomorphism \(\psi\) whose components are isomorphisms
2610	  of \(R\)-modules. Its naturality square for the inclusion \(D(f) \hookrightarrow \top\)
2611	  intertwines the restriction maps of \(\widetilde{N}\) (for \(N = \Gamma(M, \top)\)) and of \(M\).
2612	  Transporting \cref{lem:isLocalizedModule_tilde_restrict} across the two component isomorphisms
2613	  (pre- and post-composing by the linear equivalences induced by the components of \(\psi\))
2614	  identifies the restriction of \(M\) with a localization map, hence it is
2615	  \(\mathrm{IsLocalizedModule}(\mathrm{powers}\,f)\).
2616	\end{proof}
