2711	  For a sheaf \(F\) and a family of opens \(\{U_i\}\) with union \(V\), any family of sections
2712	  \(s_i \in F(U_i)\) agreeing on overlaps glues to a unique \(s \in F(V)\); and a section of \(V\)
2713	  is determined by its restrictions to a cover (\(\mathrm{eq\_of\_locally\_eq'}\)). These discharge
2714	  the existence and uniqueness obligations in the inductive step. The primed companion
